msgid "example.bad.title"
msgstr "‚ùå Don't do this"

# the placeholder is the year, i.e. "2022"
msgid "example.bad.body"
msgstr ""
"Note that Tucker could have got his answer minutes sooner, and needn't have kept Arlo waiting. In fact, Arlo could have started thinking about the question right away!\n"
"\n"
"People who do this are generally trying to be polite by not jumping right into the request, like one would in Ticket or on the Direct Messages - and that's great! But it's %1$s and chat is neither of those things. For most people, typing is much slower than talking. So despite best intentions, **you're actually just making the other person wait** for you to phrase your question, which is lost productivity (and kinda annoying).\n"
"\n"
"The same goes for:\n"
"\n"
"- \"Hello, are you around?\"\n"
"- \"hi Bunn - quick question.\"\n"
"- \"You got a sec?\"\n"
"- \"yt?\"\n"
"- \"ping\"\n"
"- etc.\n"
"\n"
"**Just ask the question!!!** üò´\n"

